    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h5 id="如何构建你自己基于以太坊的ERC20令牌并且在接下来的20分钟内启动ICO"><a href="#如何构建你自己基于以太坊的ERC20令牌并且在接下来的20分钟内启动ICO" class="headerlink" title="如何构建你自己基于以太坊的ERC20令牌并且在接下来的20分钟内启动ICO"></a>如何构建你自己基于以太坊的ERC20令牌并且在接下来的20分钟内启动ICO</h5><p>更新：我写了一本关于以太坊智能合约的书，这本书可以在<a href="https://leanpub.com/smart-contracts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LeanPub</a>上购买，如果你对了解更多关于合约和构建去中心化App感兴趣，你可以随意的尝试一下。</p><p>​    如果您正在寻找先进的东西，如预售，公开销售，折扣，目标，硬帽等，请查看我最新的文章。</p><p>最近我正在深入的研究区块链和去中心化应用以自学和提高我的知识，为了让学习过程更加有趣我决定去构建我自己基于以太坊的代币并去理解发行ICO的过程（首次铸币发行）。</p><p>​    这篇文章的目的是通过发行一个简单的demo ICO让你了解智能合约如何在以太坊中工作的。</p><p>​    让hashcode成为你讨论所有加密相关的核心，看看我们的<a href="https://hashnode.com/communities" target="_blank" rel="noopener">加密社区</a>并且加入到区块链相关的讨论中。</p><p><strong>基础</strong></p><p>这里有一些基础的术语我们将要在这篇文章中用到，如果你已经熟悉这些概念，随你跳过接下来的部分。</p><ol><li>基于以太坊 ERC20代币：在以太坊中代币可以代表任何可以贸易的物品列如货币，积分等。你可以创建你自己的基于以太坊的加密货币。此外基于这套标准的益处是你的代币可以兼容任何基于同样标准的客户端和钱包。</li><li>智能合约：智能合约是发布在以太坊区块链中自执行的代码块，他们包含数据和功能代码，合约可以做决定，和其他合约互动，存储数据，在用户间交易以太（以太坊区块链中加密货币单位）。</li><li>Solidity：一种写智能合约的语言。</li><li>MetaMask/Mist/MEW Wallet：一种可以保存你的以太和其他基于以太坊代币的数字设备。</li></ol><p>现在你已经知道了用在这篇文中的基础属于，让我们开始吧。</p><h5 id="步骤-1-代码"><a href="#步骤-1-代码" class="headerlink" title="步骤  1  代码"></a>步骤  1  代码</h5><p>打开自己喜欢的文本编辑器并且粘贴下面的代码：</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br><span class="line">32</span><br><span class="line">33</span><br><span class="line">34</span><br><span class="line">35</span><br><span class="line">36</span><br><span class="line">37</span><br><span class="line">38</span><br><span class="line">39</span><br><span class="line">40</span><br><span class="line">41</span><br><span class="line">42</span><br><span class="line">43</span><br><span class="line">44</span><br><span class="line">45</span><br><span class="line">46</span><br><span class="line">47</span><br><span class="line">48</span><br><span class="line">49</span><br><span class="line">50</span><br><span class="line">51</span><br><span class="line">52</span><br><span class="line">53</span><br><span class="line">54</span><br><span class="line">55</span><br><span class="line">56</span><br><span class="line">57</span><br><span class="line">58</span><br><span class="line">59</span><br><span class="line">60</span><br><span class="line">61</span><br><span class="line">62</span><br><span class="line">63</span><br><span class="line">64</span><br><span class="line">65</span><br><span class="line">66</span><br><span class="line">67</span><br><span class="line">68</span><br><span class="line">69</span><br><span class="line">70</span><br><span class="line">71</span><br><span class="line">72</span><br><span class="line">73</span><br><span class="line">74</span><br><span class="line">75</span><br><span class="line">76</span><br><span class="line">77</span><br><span class="line">78</span><br><span class="line">79</span><br><span class="line">80</span><br><span class="line">81</span><br><span class="line">82</span><br><span class="line">83</span><br><span class="line">84</span><br><span class="line">85</span><br><span class="line">86</span><br><span class="line">87</span><br><span class="line">88</span><br><span class="line">89</span><br><span class="line">90</span><br><span class="line">91</span><br><span class="line">92</span><br><span class="line">93</span><br><span class="line">94</span><br><span class="line">95</span><br><span class="line">96</span><br><span class="line">97</span><br><span class="line">98</span><br><span class="line">99</span><br><span class="line">100</span><br><span class="line">101</span><br><span class="line">102</span><br><span class="line">103</span><br><span class="line">104</span><br><span class="line">105</span><br><span class="line">106</span><br><span class="line">107</span><br><span class="line">108</span><br><span class="line">109</span><br><span class="line">110</span><br><span class="line">111</span><br><span class="line">112</span><br><span class="line">113</span><br><span class="line">114</span><br><span class="line">115</span><br><span class="line">116</span><br><span class="line">117</span><br><span class="line">118</span><br><span class="line">119</span><br><span class="line">120</span><br><span class="line">121</span><br><span class="line">122</span><br><span class="line">123</span><br><span class="line">124</span><br><span class="line">125</span><br><span class="line">126</span><br><span class="line">127</span><br><span class="line">128</span><br><span class="line">129</span><br><span class="line">130</span><br><span class="line">131</span><br><span class="line">132</span><br><span class="line">133</span><br><span class="line">134</span><br><span class="line">135</span><br><span class="line">136</span><br><span class="line">137</span><br><span class="line">138</span><br><span class="line">139</span><br><span class="line">140</span><br><span class="line">141</span><br><span class="line">142</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">pragma solidity ^0.4.4;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">contract Token &#123;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @return total amount of tokens</span><br><span class="line">    function totalSupply() constant returns (uint256 supply) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _owner The address from which the balance will be retrieved</span><br><span class="line">    /// @return The balance</span><br><span class="line">    function balanceOf(address _owner) constant returns (uint256 balance) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @notice send `_value` token to `_to` from `msg.sender`</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _to The address of the recipient</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _value The amount of token to be transferred</span><br><span class="line">    /// @return Whether the transfer was successful or not</span><br><span class="line">    function transfer(address _to, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @notice send `_value` token to `_to` from `_from` on the condition it is approved by `_from`</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _from The address of the sender</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _to The address of the recipient</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _value The amount of token to be transferred</span><br><span class="line">    /// @return Whether the transfer was successful or not</span><br><span class="line">    function transferFrom(address _from, address _to, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @notice `msg.sender` approves `_addr` to spend `_value` tokens</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _spender The address of the account able to transfer the tokens</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _value The amount of wei to be approved for transfer</span><br><span class="line">    /// @return Whether the approval was successful or not</span><br><span class="line">    function approve(address _spender, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _owner The address of the account owning tokens</span><br><span class="line">    /// @param _spender The address of the account able to transfer the tokens</span><br><span class="line">    /// @return Amount of remaining tokens allowed to spent</span><br><span class="line">    function allowance(address _owner, address _spender) constant returns (uint256 remaining) &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    event Transfer(address indexed _from, address indexed _to, uint256 _value);</span><br><span class="line">    event Approval(address indexed _owner, address indexed _spender, uint256 _value);</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">contract StandardToken is Token &#123;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function transfer(address _to, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        //Default assumes totalSupply can&apos;t be over max (2^256 - 1).</span><br><span class="line">        //If your token leaves out totalSupply and can issue more tokens as time goes on, you need to check if it doesn&apos;t wrap.</span><br><span class="line">        //Replace the if with this one instead.</span><br><span class="line">        //if (balances[msg.sender] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; balances[_to] + _value &gt; balances[_to]) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        if (balances[msg.sender] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; _value &gt; 0) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">            balances[msg.sender] -= _value;</span><br><span class="line">            balances[_to] += _value;</span><br><span class="line">            Transfer(msg.sender, _to, _value);</span><br><span class="line">            return true;</span><br><span class="line">        &#125; else &#123; return false; &#125;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function transferFrom(address _from, address _to, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        //same as above. Replace this line with the following if you want to protect against wrapping uints.</span><br><span class="line">        //if (balances[_from] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; allowed[_from][msg.sender] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; balances[_to] + _value &gt; balances[_to]) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        if (balances[_from] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; allowed[_from][msg.sender] &gt;= _value &amp;&amp; _value &gt; 0) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">            balances[_to] += _value;</span><br><span class="line">            balances[_from] -= _value;</span><br><span class="line">            allowed[_from][msg.sender] -= _value;</span><br><span class="line">            Transfer(_from, _to, _value);</span><br><span class="line">            return true;</span><br><span class="line">        &#125; else &#123; return false; &#125;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function balanceOf(address _owner) constant returns (uint256 balance) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        return balances[_owner];</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function approve(address _spender, uint256 _value) returns (bool success) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        allowed[msg.sender][_spender] = _value;</span><br><span class="line">        Approval(msg.sender, _spender, _value);</span><br><span class="line">        return true;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function allowance(address _owner, address _spender) constant returns (uint256 remaining) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">      return allowed[_owner][_spender];</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    mapping (address =&gt; uint256) balances;</span><br><span class="line">    mapping (address =&gt; mapping (address =&gt; uint256)) allowed;</span><br><span class="line">    uint256 public totalSupply;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">contract HashnodeTestCoin is StandardToken &#123; // CHANGE THIS. Update the contract name.</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /* Public variables of the token */</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /*</span><br><span class="line">    NOTE:</span><br><span class="line">    The following variables are OPTIONAL vanities. One does not have to include them.</span><br><span class="line">    They allow one to customise the token contract &amp; in no way influences the core functionality.</span><br><span class="line">    Some wallets/interfaces might not even bother to look at this information.</span><br><span class="line">    */</span><br><span class="line">    string public name;                   // Token Name</span><br><span class="line">    uint8 public decimals;                // How many decimals to show. To be standard complicant keep it 18</span><br><span class="line">    string public symbol;                 // An identifier: eg SBX, XPR etc..</span><br><span class="line">    string public version = &apos;H1.0&apos;; </span><br><span class="line">    uint256 public unitsOneEthCanBuy;     // How many units of your coin can be bought by 1 ETH?</span><br><span class="line">    uint256 public totalEthInWei;         // WEI is the smallest unit of ETH (the equivalent of cent in USD or satoshi in BTC). We&apos;ll store the total ETH raised via our ICO here.  </span><br><span class="line">    address public fundsWallet;           // Where should the raised ETH go?</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    // This is a constructor function </span><br><span class="line">    // which means the following function name has to match the contract name declared above</span><br><span class="line">    function HashnodeTestCoin() &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        balances[msg.sender] = 1000000000000000000000;               // Give the creator all initial tokens. This is set to 1000 for example. If you want your initial tokens to be X and your decimal is 5, set this value to X * 100000. (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        totalSupply = 1000000000000000000000;                        // Update total supply (1000 for example) (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        name = &quot;HashnodeTestCoin&quot;;                                   // Set the name for display purposes (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        decimals = 18;                                               // Amount of decimals for display purposes (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        symbol = &quot;HTCN&quot;;                                             // Set the symbol for display purposes (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        unitsOneEthCanBuy = 10;                                      // Set the price of your token for the ICO (CHANGE THIS)</span><br><span class="line">        fundsWallet = msg.sender;                                    // The owner of the contract gets ETH</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    function() payable&#123;</span><br><span class="line">        totalEthInWei = totalEthInWei + msg.value;</span><br><span class="line">        uint256 amount = msg.value * unitsOneEthCanBuy;</span><br><span class="line">        require(balances[fundsWallet] &gt;= amount);</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        balances[fundsWallet] = balances[fundsWallet] - amount;</span><br><span class="line">        balances[msg.sender] = balances[msg.sender] + amount;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        Transfer(fundsWallet, msg.sender, amount); // Broadcast a message to the blockchain</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        //Transfer ether to fundsWallet</span><br><span class="line">        fundsWallet.transfer(msg.value);                               </span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    /* Approves and then calls the receiving contract */</span><br><span class="line">    function approveAndCall(address _spender, uint256 _value, bytes _extraData) returns (bool success) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        allowed[msg.sender][_spender] = _value;</span><br><span class="line">        Approval(msg.sender, _spender, _value);</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        //call the receiveApproval function on the contract you want to be notified. This crafts the function signature manually so one doesn&apos;t have to include a contract in here just for this.</span><br><span class="line">        //receiveApproval(address _from, uint256 _value, address _tokenContract, bytes _extraData)</span><br><span class="line">        //it is assumed that when does this that the call *should* succeed, otherwise one would use vanilla approve instead.</span><br><span class="line">        if(!_spender.call(bytes4(bytes32(sha3(&quot;receiveApproval(address,uint256,address,bytes)&quot;))), msg.sender, _value, this, _extraData)) &#123; throw; &#125;</span><br><span class="line">        return true;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>基于来自<a href="https://github.com/ConsenSys/Token-Factory/blob/master/contracts/StandardToken.sol" target="_blank" rel="noopener">令牌工厂</a>的原始来源。</p><p>​    上面的代码用Solidity语言构建了一个简单的ERC20代币，代码注释很好并且非常容易理解，一旦你将代码粘贴到了你的文本编辑器中，找到这些字：”Change This”，这些是需要你基于自己代币特征去改变的，在上面的例子中，我把我的代币命名为 HashnodeTestCoin(HTCN)，总的供应量不超过1000，但是人们可以持有代币的最小0.000000000000000001 ，由于他有18个小数的位置。此外，合约的拥有者（一个执行合约的人）持有所有的初始代币，我设置的ICO价格如下：</p><p>​    1ETH=10HTCN</p><p>​    他的意思是，如果一个人给这个智能合约发送了一个以太坊，他们将要得到10个HTCN。</p><h4 id="Step-2"><a href="#Step-2" class="headerlink" title="Step 2"></a>Step 2</h4><p>​    下载一个谷歌的插件 MetaMask去生成一个钱包，这将是智能合约的拥有者，除此之外你还可以选择Mist或者<a href="https://myetherwallet.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">My Ether Wallet</a>，为了简单起见这里让我们在这个项目中用Meat Mask插件。</p><p>​    下载这个插件之后，继续并且创建一个新的受密码保护的账户，然后可以在左上角选择”Ropsten TestNet”，在我们把合约发不到主网络上之前，我们将要在测试网络上测试他并且确认每件事都按预期运行，它看起来像这样：</p><p><img src="/img/1533793594150.png" alt=""></p><p>现在我们转向Remix IDE（一个在线的Solidity编译器和调试器）并且粘贴你刚刚修改的代码，忽略任何你看到的警告，接下来转到设置，如果选中了”Enable Optimizations”，则取消选中。</p><p>现在转向”Run”选项卡并点击你代币上的create按钮。</p><p><img src="/img/1533793998119.png" alt=""></p><p>​    一旦你点击了创建，MetaMask将要提示你去买一些测试的以太币并且提交这个交易，他看起来是这样：</p><p><img src="/img/1533794404350.png" alt=""></p><p>只要确认你在Ropsten测试网络上不在主网络上然后点击提交，现在再次打开MetaMask然后点击第一条交易，它将要带你去Etherscan，在哪你可以查看正在进行的交易，他也许话费30秒中去提交这个交易，一旦提交成功，它看起来像下面这样：</p><p><img src="/img/1533794770720.png" alt=""></p><p>Viola!! 你仅仅发布了你的合约，记住上面交易单中的这个”to”地址，这是你的合约地址。</p><p>现在是验证你的合约是否有效的时候了。</p><h4 id="Step-3"><a href="#Step-3" class="headerlink" title="Step 3"></a>Step 3</h4><p>​    理想状态下如果你设置的没问题你应该可以收到所有的初始代币（在我的案例中是1000），当你把它添加到你的钱包时。因此，你需要拷贝这个合约地址，转到MetaMask–&gt;添加代币并且粘贴地址,它看起来像这样：</p><p><img src="/img/1533795451967.png" alt=""></p><p>点击Add并刷新MetaMask，你现在应该可以看到所有的初始供应量（在我的钱包中是1000HTCN）。</p><h4 id="Step-4"><a href="#Step-4" class="headerlink" title="Step 4"></a>Step 4</h4><p>​    现在一切都完美了，我们只要去验证一下我们的智能合约，让区块链中的每个人都可以阅读和理解，因为它总是可以帮助建立信任，所以验证总是一个好的实践。</p><p>​    现在转到我们的合约地址，并且点击Contract Code标签。</p><p><img src="/img/1533796027383.png" alt=""></p><p>​    现在点击”verify and publish “链接，你一旦跳转到了新的页面，填充一下细节，例如编译版本，启动优化等，并且粘贴我们在第一步编译的Solidity源代码。</p><p><img src="/img/1533796352380.png" alt=""></p><p>​    确认选择的编译器版本和你再第一次编译代码时的那个版本匹配。现在点击”verify and publish “，如果成功，他将要生成字节码和API，如下所示：</p><p><img src="/img/1533796816583.png" alt=""></p><p>​    祝贺，现在任何人可以访问你的合约地址和阅读源代码。</p><h4 id="Step-5"><a href="#Step-5" class="headerlink" title="Step 5"></a>Step 5</h4><p>​    发布你的合约到生产环境，你仅仅需要在MetaMask中切换测试网络到主网络（在左上角的位置）并且重复第2到4步，请你注意的是在那里部署你的合约你将要话费真实的以太币，因此，你还有充分准备好之前不要部署你的合约（合约是不可变的并且不能更新的一旦你部署后），我们在本教程中继续使用测试网络。</p><h5 id="用以太币买代币"><a href="#用以太币买代币" class="headerlink" title="用以太币买代币"></a>用以太币买代币</h5><p>作为ICO的一部分，你的用户将要通过支付以太币的方式在你那里购买代币，你还记的你在发布合约的时候设置的价格是1ETH=10HTCH ? 因此，你的用户想要通过你的ICO在你那里购买10 HTCH，他们需要支付1ETH，让我们测试它。</p><p>​    转到MetaMask，创建一个新的账户并且用一些测试以太币加载它，一旦这个账户被加载了，点击”Send”并且填写上你的合约地址，在数字字段中，输入2（ETH）。</p><p><img src="/img/1533798108891.png" alt=""></p><p>​    接下来，发送两个以太币给你的合约地址，并且等待这个交易被确认，刷新MetaMask并且在几秒后检查你的代币数量，这个新的测试账户将要得到20个HTCN（你的配置不同可能会有所不同），并且合约拥有者（你）应该有980个（类似数量的）代币。</p><p><img src="/img/1533798402860.png" alt=""></p><p>此外，你将要收到2个以太币。</p><p>恭喜成功。</p><h5 id="发行一个ICO页面"><a href="#发行一个ICO页面" class="headerlink" title="发行一个ICO页面"></a>发行一个ICO页面</h5><p>​    为了展示通过你的ICO项目筹集到了多少以太币，我们将要用到一个被称作web3.js 的javascript类库在我们的项目中。</p><p>​    转向hash节点测试ICO硬币，检查代码的最后一个script标签，他是相当的简单并且仅仅用到了web3.js和来自你合约的ABI。</p><p><img src="/img/1533799325329.png" alt=""></p><p>​    恭喜你走了这么远，一定要记住，一个真实的生产环境的交易合约和ICO需要付出很大的努力和通过全面测试的支持，虽然这个教程给你提供了为ICO写合约的概述，但是他不能用于生产级别的部署，没有通过全面的测试不要在主网络上发布它!</p><p>​    谢谢你都这篇文章，如果你有任何的问题，请随意的评论。</p><p>​    有关于区块链相关的问题？在hash节点上检验这些<a href="https://hashnode.com/communities" target="_blank" rel="noopener">加密社区</a>，并开始讨论。</p><p>原文：<a href="https://hashnode.com/post/how-to-build-your-own-ethereum-based-erc20-token-and-launch-an-ico-in-next-20-minutes-cjbcpwzec01c93awtbij90uzn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://hashnode.com/post/how-to-build-your-own-ethereum-based-erc20-token-and-launch-an-ico-in-next-20-minutes-cjbcpwzec01c93awtbij90uzn</a></p>]]></content>
    
